title: jewelpet_(creature)
body:
Titular species of magical [[creature]] from the [[Jewelpet (series)|]] series. They are magical pets who reside in Jewel Land and pair up with humans to find magical jewels.

Jewelpets are considered to be popular [[chibikemo]] characters, as they usually walk on two legs by default, though they can also take on a quadruped form if they wish.

title: shirogane_noel_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[hololive]]'s [[Shirogane Noel]].

It consists of a [[short dress|short]], [[collared dress|collared]], [[pleated dress|pleated]] white-and-blue [[armored dress]] (although sometimes it's depicted as a separate shirt and skirt) with a [[puffy sleeves]] and a noticeably large [[cleavage cutout]] to the right hand side (described by Noel as a "ventilation"), a small white [[tabard]] or [[pelvic curtain]], a white [[waist cape]] a [[brown belt|brown]] [[leather belt]] with a [[belt pouch]] and [[black thighhighs]]. She also wears an [[armor]] consisting of a [[single pauldron]], a [[chest guard]] held with a [[chest harness]] and a [[chest strap]], [[vambraces]], [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]] and [[greaves]]. In her hair, she has dark grey [[tiara]] with gold accents.
She also carries a [[mace]] on her waist.

h4. Appearance

* !post #3589683: Profile
* !post #3803098: Merchandise

title: one_side_up
body: A variation of [[two side up]] in which some locks of hair are tied up on one side while the rest hangs normally. Neither length or volume of the tied up hair nor that of the other free-flowing hair matters for tagging purposes, only that the remaining hair falls down loosely. Not to be confused with [[side ponytail]], where the majority of one's hair—save for [[sidelocks]]—is pulled up into a ponytail that leaves no hair falling loosely. If the hair is not tied up but just sticking out on its own, tag as [[side ahoge]]. h5. Examples * !post #6414776: short hair, short side up * !post #6426051: short hair, long side up * !post #7775296: medium hair, short side up * !post #6373249: medium hair, long side up * !post #6431000: long hair, short side up * !post #6511326: long hair, long side up * !post #7158018: [[single side bun]] h5. Not [[one side up]] * !post #7237036: [[side ponytail]] * !post #7612721: [[low side ponytail]]

title: suica
body:
[b]Super Urban Intelligent Card[/b], a type of smart card used by [[East Japan Railway Company]] for fares in Kantou region. The name is a play on the word "[i]suika[/i]", ie. watermelon, and also the combination of the ideophone "[i]sui sui[/i]", ie. "moving smoothly", and "card". Thanks to the good recognisability of the name, it's well suited for puns.

title: final_fantasy
body:
A popular, long-running role-playing game series by [[Square Enix]].

Final Fantasy first appeared in 1987 in reaction to Enix's [[Dragon Quest]]. Contrarily to what is often said, while Square wasn't doing great at the time, the first game wasn't made as a last ditch attempt to save the company. It did end up being a great commercial success and as a result, subsequent titles (each set in a different universe) were published ever since.

When tagging the first game, use [[Final Fantasy I]].

body:

Don't tag things like [[terror bird]]s or giant baby chickens.

title: colored_extremities
body:
A type of [[multicolored skin]] where extremities are differently colored than the rest of the body. Commonly seen in the hands and/or feet of a demonic character fading to black. This can be anything from only the finger tips being discolored to extending from the toes all the way to the thigh and be a gradual fade or sharp transition.

This does not include wearing wearing [[gloves]] or [[socks]], nor [[feathers]], [[fur]] or [[scales]] on differently colored skin (If the skin underneath fades to match the color it does count).

title: matsudaira_nobutsuna_(fate)
body:
Supporting character in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s chapter [i][[Ooku (fate/grand order)|Tokugawa Restoration Labyrinth, Ooku]][/i]. A concept that opposed [[Kama_(fate)|]]'s power was imbued in his soul and a spell was engraved in his body to transform his organs into [[hanafuda]] cards, which made him incessantly cough blood. He acted as a double agent, serving Kama while scattering the cards throughout the labyrinth, aiding Chaldea with their power. Nobutsuna later sacrifices himself and a blade emerges from his body for [[yagyuu_munenori_(fate)|Yagyuu]] to wield, gaining advantage over Kama.

He also appears briefly in the opening animation for Fate/Samurai Remnant, but nowhere else in the game.

[B]Character Design[/b]: [[Furumi Showichi]]

body:

title: sweatdrop
body:
A single large sweatdrop usually used to depict a character who is [[nervous]] or [[embarrassed]] in a situation.

If the single sweatdrop is small/normal-sized, use [[small sweatdrop]] instead.

If the single sweatdrop is especially huge and unrealistic, and appears on the character's side or back of the head (as might be seen in [[1990s_(style)|1990s]] anime like [[bishoujo senshi sailor moon|Sailor Moon]]), consider using [[comedic sweatdrop]] instead.

If there is more than one sweatdrop, use [[sweat]].

title: souryuu_asuka_langley
body:
A character from [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]], daughter of [[Souryuu Kyouko Zeppelin]].

She is a 14-year-old of mixed [[germany|German]] and [[Japan]]ese descent, and [[united_States|American]] by nationality. The red hot pilot of [[Eva 02|Evangelion Unit 02]], she is proud in nature and a tough girl with attitude. She is described as being [[tsundere]] for [[Ikari Shinji]] and the two may be considered a canon pairing as director [[Anno Hideaki]] has stated to prefer the two of them together. 

See {{Souryuu_Asuka_Langley Rebuild_of_Evangelion}} for Asuka Shikinami Langley from the [[Rebuild of Evangelion]] movies.

body:

title: romani_archaman
body:
[[Fate/Grand Order]] character.

Chief medical officer at the [[Chaldea Security Organization]] and a very relaxed person. Friends with [[Leonardo da Vinci (Fate)|]] and is a devoted fan of [[Magi Mari|Magi☆Mari]].

[spoiler]He turns out to be the true Servant [[Solomon (fate)|Solomon]], who uses the wish gained by winning the Holy Grail War to incarnate himself as a human in order to experience all that he hadn't in life. He uses his final Noble Phantasm, Ars Nova, to erase himself from existence and give the heroes a fighting chance at defeating Goetia at the final battle in the Solomon singularity.[/spoiler]

Not to be confused with [[Chaldea no Mono]], who has orange eyes instead.

title: donkey_kong_country
body:
[quote][i][tn]"The king of swing, the thrilla gorilla, the prime primate; it's Donkey Kong! But this is not your father's Donkey Kong! Although he is a relative of the classic arcade character, Country's Donkey Kong is a totally new character, with a new look, new moves, and a new attitude."[/tn][/i][/quote][tn]—Donkey Kong Country Instruction Booklet, page 12[/tn]

A 2D platforming game developed by Rare Ltd, released on the [[Super Nintendo]] in 1994. It stars [[Donkey Kong]] and his buddy [[Diddy Kong]] in their quest to trek the entirety of Donkey Kong Island in order to recover their stolen [[banana]]s from an antagonistic [[crocodilian]] race known as the Kremlings. 

This title rebooted the [i][[Donkey Kong_(series)|]][/i] franchise, changing Donkey Kong from a villain to a hero, giving him a new design, an entirely new setting, and a new cast of supporting characters and enemies.

body:
Spin-off of the [i][[Wario Land]][/i] series and the only 3D entry of the entire Wario franchise, released on the [[Gamecube|Nintendo Gamecube]] and developed by [[treasure_(developer)|Treasure Co., Ltd]].

[[Wario]], surrounded by treasures he's pilfered from all around the world and a newly constructed castle, is flipped upside down when one of the jewels he stole was actually the [[Black Jewel]], an evil that destroyed a civilization long ago. The Black Jewel begins transforming his castle into it's own world and turns all of his treasures into monsters, making Wario vow for revenge.

title: dark_elf
body:
An [[Elf]] sub-type who are said to be troublesome to others or affiliate themselves with evil and/or dark sides. In some works, they are treated as a separate but related species of elves and are not necessarily evil.

Dark elf appearances vary from depiction to depiction. Many, such as those inspired by [[Dungeons & Dragons]] tend to have [[colored skin]] in various tones of [[blue skin|blue]], [[grey skin|grey]], or [[purple skin| purple]]. Others like the [[Dark Eldar]] from [[Warhammer 40k]] tend to have extremely [[pale skin|pale]] or [[white skin]]. Typical dark elves in many Japanese copyrights instead just have [[dark skin]].

This tag can also be applied for elves from copyrights where they have none of the above yet it is their title as a character.

h4. See also

* [[elf]]
* [[Tag Group:Legendary Creatures]]

title: nia_(xenoblade)
body:
[[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]] character.

Named [b]Niyah[/b] in the Japanese version.

A member of the main cast. She is a Gormotti Driver whose Blade is [[dromarch (xenoblade)|Byakko]] (Dromarch).

She has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] with [[blunt bangs]], [[yellow eyes]] and [[cat ears]]. She wears a [[yellow bodysuit]] with [[white gloves]]. She usually has [[small breasts]] or a [[flat chest]], depending on the artist.

She also has [[facial mark]]s (a short white cat-like stripe from her forehead and each cheek), but artists frequently forget them.

She wields [[chakram]]s in battle.

[spoiler]Later revealed to be a Flesh Eater Blade. See [[nia (blade) (xenoblade)|Nia (Blade)]].[/spoiler] The DLC also gives her a swimsuit costume called [[Nia (fancy sundress) (xenoblade)|Fancy Sundress]].

Appears in [[Xenoblade Chronicles 3]] as the [b]Queen of Agnus.[/b] [spoilers]She is recruitable as a Hero in the postgame.[/spoiler]

title: cyborg
body:
An organism that is made up of both [b]cyb[/b]ernetic and [b]org[/b]anic components. In anime, this generally refers to humans that have been altered to be partially [[robot]]ic.

It can be difficult to tell a cyborg apart from an [[android]], especially when dealing with [[original]] characters and those whose origins are unknown. In cases like these, one should examine any visible robotic components. If they appear to be added-on or function as [[prosthesis|prosthetics]], that character is likely a cyborg. If you are unable to determine whether the character is a cyborg or purely robotic, it's best to tag them as [[android]] until more information can be found.

title: kaiju
body:
[b]Kaiju[/b] (怪獣) is a Japanese word that means "strange beast," but often translated in English as "monster." Specifically, it is used to refer to a genre of tokusatsu entertainment involving giant monsters.

Related terms include kaiju eiga (怪獣映画, monster movie), a film featuring kaiju, kaijin (怪人, humanoid monsters) and daikaiju (大怪獣, giant monster), specifically meaning the larger variety of monsters.

The most famous kaiju is [[Godzilla]]. Other well-known kaiju include [[Mothra]], [[Anguirus]], [[Rodan]], [[Gamera]], and [[King Ghidorah]].

h4. See also

* [[Gamera (series)|]]
* [[Godzilla (series)|]]
* [[Pacific Rim]]
* [[Ultra Series]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Kaiju":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaiju]

title: loincloth
body:
Any of several ancient styles of garment designed to cover the genitals. Usually made from a folded and tied length of cloth, sometimes held in place by a belt. If it has a dangling length of cloth hanging in front and/or or behind, that part is called, for Danbooru's purposes, a [[pelvic curtain]]. 

[[Fundoshi]] are a range of specifically Japanese styles of loincloth. The loincloth's modern replacements are [[panties]], [[briefs]], and [[boxers]].

Both [[loincloth]] and [[fundoshi]] nowadays are used as festival clothing (usually with [[happi]], or alone) , as a [[swimsuit]] (when worn at the [[beach]]) and occasionally, as [[underwear]] (usually worm under [[kimono]], or [[Japanese armor]] etc). Make sure to use the appropriate tag when tagging them.

If the loincloth is attached to a full-body clothing garment, consider tagging [[tabard]] as well [tn](post #7734925)[/tn].

h4. See also
* [[Fundoshi]]
* [[Naked tabard]]
* [[Pelvic curtain]]
* [[Tabard]]
* [[White male swimwear]] 

h4. External links

* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loincloth

title: medic_(isekai_mokushiroku_mynoghra)
body:
One of Mynoghra's normal units produced by Eternal Nation's Clinic facility. They're tall humanoid creatures wrapped entirely in black with a [[plague doctor]] motif. Concealed beneath their robes they have large eyes, shriveled flesh, bent limbs, swollen lumps with darkened skin and ferocious claws, as they're actually Brain Eaters. They're obsessed with humans to the point of wearing the raw flesh they skin off their victims and they refer to humans as "hueman". Contrary to their appearance, they're loud, cheerful and use overly exaggerated gestures.

Normal units don't have unique names, but Takuto named three Medics as Ichiro, Jiro and Saburo.

title: wario_land:_shake_it!
body:
The final entry in the [i][[Wario Land]][/i] series and developed primarily outside of [[Nintendo]] by Good-Feel, released on the [[Wii]].

The Shake Dimension is under peril due to the marauding of the [[Shake King]] and kidnapping of [[Queen Merelda]]. [[Wario]] is uninterested about the plight of the escaped [[Merfle_(wario_land)|]]'s homeworld until it's mentioned that the Shake King also stole the Bottomless Coin Sack, which Wario now wants for himself. Making a deal, Wario has a change of heart and agrees to help the Merfle to acquire this treasure.

Notable for bringing back a redesigned [[Captain Syrup]].
other_names: ワリオランドシェイク

title: shop_owner_(wario_land)
body:
A character in [[Wario Land 4]]. A mysterious entity that runs the Item Shop before each Boss Door. 

The entity will use the items purchased to damage the boss preemptively before the battle begins. Some of the items purchased do not give you a physical item, but instead will have the Shop Owner transform into different creatures to do the damage themselves. These transformations are the [i]Black Dog[/i], the [i]Large Lips[/i], the [i]Big Fist[/i] and the [i]Black Dragon[/i].

h6.All items:
* Apple Bomb
* Blast Cannon
* Vizorman
* Bugle
* [[Black_Dog_(wario_land)|Black Dog]]
* [[Large_Lips_(wario_land)|Large Lips]]
* [[big_fist_(wario_land)|Big Fist]]
* [[black_dragon_(wario_land)|Black Dragon]]

You can also order a free "Smile", but it doesn't do anything. 

[spoiler]Its true identity is that of [[Princess Shokora]].[/spoiler]

title: azur_lane:_slow_ahead
body:
An [[Azur Lane]] slice-of-life manga by [[Hori (hori no su)|]], set around the schooling and daily adventures of the starter destroyer shipgirls [[Javelin (Azur Lane)|]], [[Ayanami (Azur Lane)|]], [[Laffey (Azur Lane)|]] and their advisor [[Z23 (Azur Lane)|]].

Adapted into an anime in early 2021 that is not only different in genre and emotional tone to the original [i]Azur Lane[/i] anime, but also made at least partly in-house, as Candybox has studio credit alongside Yostar Pictures. The series also features episode [[end card]]s drawn by fan artists.

Use this tag for the actual 4koma itself or for things referencing either the anime or 4koma (For example, [[North Carolina (Azur Lane)|North Carolina]]’s bunny suit from both, which predates [[North Carolina (The Heart's Desire) (Azur Lane)|The Heart's Desire]], would only count if it's black with the outfit tips down or black with her jacket over it). The tag can also be used for skins that originated in the 4koma before becoming available in the game, such as Javelin's [[Javelin (Slow Ahead!) (Azur Lane)|Slow Ahead!]] or the starters' fantasy/RPG-themed skins.

title: praise_the_sun
body:
[i]"The sun is a wondrous body, like a magnificent father! If only I could be so grossly incandescent..."[/i]

A pose involving stretching out one's arms upwards and tilting one's head towards the sky, as if one was ready to embrace the sun. 

While this pose is most commonly associated with [[Dark Souls I|Dark Souls's]] [[Solaire of Astora]] and the Warriors of Sunlight, it first appeared in [[Demon's Souls]] as an alternate animation for casting miracles while equipping the Ring of Sincere Prayer.

The emoticon associated with it is [b]\o/[/b]. The Solaire specific version is [b]\[T]/[/b].

title: yukimura_ryuuko_(ryuuko)
body: Original character belonging to "Ryuuko/BasedJunyou":[https://twitter.com/BasedJunyou], usually seen in commissioned artwork by various artists. She is depicted as Ryuuko's [[female commander (azur lane)|commander]] character, hailing from the Maple Monarchy ([[Azur Lane]]'s representation of [[Canada]], mentioned in [[Fortune (Azur Lane)|Fortune]]'s quotes). The character creator also came up with the following biography for the character in a Reddit post of the first art featuring her (Post #5608350), since deleted: [expand=Biography] * Name: Ryūko Yukimura (雪村 龍子 – Yukimura Ryūko) * Date of birth: February 14, 1996 * Place of birth: Seneca, Ontario, Maple Monarchy * Nationality: Bangladeshi-Canadian * Naval college graduation date: May 1, 2018 * Age: 27, as of February 2023 * Height: 5'3" (160 cm) * Weight: 115 lbs (52 kg) * Rank: Admiral (January 2023-present) * Appearance: As depicted in the drawing! * Three sizes: 84-56-83 * Default attire: As depicted in the drawing! * Hobbies: Sports, video games, astronomy, digital art, model ships, naval history, MMA, fashion (of all kinds) * Family: HMS Prince of Wales (wife), Caroline Beau (adoptive mother), Ichiro Yukimura (paternal grandfather, deceased), unnamed deceased biological parents * CV: [[Mizuki Nana|Nana Mizuki]] * Description A renowned flag officer known as the Dragon of Azur Lane, Ryūko Yukimura is the overall fleet commander of Port Pacific – a naval base at the island of O'ahu, Hawaii. At the tender age of twenty-three, “Yuko” was promoted from Lieutenant (OF-2) to Commodore (OF-6) as the solution the Wisdom Cube Affinity Project – a confidential research endeavour which aimed to seek exceptionally competent Kansen commanders, by virtue of their inherent ‘match’ with shipgirls. In September 2019, an attack on Port Pacific (modern day Pearl Harbour) by the Sakura Empire mobilized Azur Lane. Thereafter, a bitter eighteen-month conflict with the powerful island nation began. Yuko’s prodigous handling of the ensuing conflict, deployment of strategy, and peerless care for his Kansen subordinates catapulted her through the flag officer ranks as Port Pacific stymied the Sakura Empire’s ambitions. Due to her unprecedented ascent through the ranks – and by virtue of her given name – she was awarded her nickname by the Empire admiralty. In 2014 – when she was eighteen – Yuko’s hometown was obliterated by a Siren attack. The invaders, who had used the St. Lawrence River as a buffer, opened a portal at Lake Ontario. The only reason she survived is because she decided to go to work earlier than normal that day (she worked at a retail store which had an underground bunker in case of emergency – thanks to the CEO’s paranoia about Sirens and other disasters). Riddled with Survivor’s Guilt and PTSD, she had thrown herself into her studies/training while enrolled at the Peterborough Naval Academy. Despite counseling, psychiatry, and medication he was unable to make friends with his peers at the academy – who froze her out due to a lack of understanding of her conditions (that Yuko, in turn, never properly explained to begin with as it was too sensitive a topic). By her senior year at the academy, however, she had become the undisputed number one cadet in many years – her hard work having paid off. Her only emotional support was her instructor, then-Commodore Caroline Beau – who often conversed with her outside of training hours. Yuko takes a sympathetic, informal stance to her work and understands the immense responsibility that her position entails. In spite of this, her words are nevertheless firm, demanding, and resolute – delivering the comprehension that she wants the absolute best for those around her. Outside of work hours, she is playful and teasing – occasionally making references to pop culture and internet memes. In spite of this, she is also shown to be quite deceptive; as demonstrated in Kitsune’s Oath, withholding Subject Blossom from Akagi but eventually introducing her in the cleanest manner possible – earning her the everlasting respect of the Sakura girls at base. With the help of his beloved port, Yuko eventually overcomes the horrors of her past – and challenges the future with a renewed focus. Here’s the list of her service medals (depicted as undress ribbons), in order of precedence: 1) [[Victoria Cross]] (VC) – Awarded following the defeat of IJN Taihou, IJN Shoukaku, and IJN Zuikaku (among other forces) following the Second Battle of Midway (April 2021). This is the highest honour a Maple Monarchy citizen can receive. 2) Cross of Valour (CV) – Awarded following the defeat of IJN Jintsuu and her forces near the waters of American Samoa (December 2020). This is the second-highest honour a Maple Monarchy citizen can receive. 3) Officer of the Order of Canada (OC) – Awarded by virtue of recognition for her outstanding contribution to the Maple Monarchy, by way of advancing her nation’s interests. Awarded in August 2020. 4) Commander of the Order of Military Merit (CMM) – Recognized for her outstanding contribution to the Maple Monarchy by way of consistently advancing her nation’s military interests. Awarded on August 2020. 5) Member of the Order of Ontario (OOnt) – Awarded to longtime residents of Ontario, who have demonstrated a high level of individual excellence and achievement in any field. In Yuko’s case it is her service to Azur Lane. Awarded in May 2020. 6) Star of Military Valour (SMV) – Awarded following the Battle of the Solomon Islands (May 2020); intended to honour those who have shown conspicuous acts of valour in the face of enemy hostility. 7) Star of Courage (SC) – Awarded following the First Battle of Midway (September 2019). 8) Meritorious Service Cross (military division, MSC) – Awarded in recognition by carrying out meritorious acts bringing benefit and honour for Azur Lane and the Maple Monarchy. Awarded in February 2020. 9) General Campaign Star (GCS) – Awarded following numerous Siren incursions near Hawaii in late 2019. Some other details (meta or otherwise) about Yuko: 1) Her nickname is a reference to Kazuma Kiryu. 2) She shares her favourite hobbies with me. 3) She is actually the gender-bent version of my main SKK OC, Tatsuya Yukimura (“Yuki”). Who, in turn, is completely based on me – if I had grown up in AL's world (well, my version of it). You can read their tale here. 4) Her grandfather immigrated to the Maple Monarchy in the 1960s with his wife. He was a Sakura Empire otaku, so he changed family name (and his) to Yukimura. 5) In a very special universe, she’s the brother-in-law of ArchiveSlave’s SKK OC – Alexander Cochrane. [/expand]

title: snake_eyes_(character)
body:
A character from the [[G.I. Joe]] toy line, comic books, cartoon and live action film series. 

[b]Snake Eyes[/b] (also released as [b]Snake-Eyes[/b]) is one of the original and most known members of the G.I. Joe Team. 

A lone silent commando clad in a black outfit and mask, Snake Eyes is an expert in unorthodox [[martial arts]] and advanced [[close-quarters combat]], hand-to-hand combat, infiltration, stealth and firearms. He is one of the most prominent characters in the G.I. Joe franchise, having appeared in every series of the franchise since its inception. 

He never speaks and only communicates through hand gestures. To this day, nobody knows if he can actually say a word. 

Snake-Eyes debuted as an [[action figure]] in 1982. His figure is considered the most popular G.I. Joe toy ever, with 68 different versions released as of 2014.

He is portrayed by actor/stuntman "Ray Park":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ray_Park in the 2009 live-action film [i]"G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_The_Rise_of_Cobra [/i] and the 2013 sequel [i]"G.I. Joe: Retaliation":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_Retaliation].[/i]

h4.See also
* [[Black Noir]]

h4. External links

* "[i]Silent Interlude[/i] textless comic":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WIGjpjV4wBY

title: gouf
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[b]MS-07B Gouf[/b]

A blue, mono-eyed [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]] specifically designed for [[close-quarters combat]]. It has a distinct horn on its head, spiked shoulders, and a tentacle whip which emerges from its right arm. Notably piloted by [[Ramba Ral]].

A variation known as the [[Gouf Custom]] is piloted by [[Norris Packard]] from [[Gundam 08th MS Team]]. The Gouf was redesigned for [[Gundam SEED Destiny]], and is known as the [[GOUF Ignited]]. It is most notably piloted by [[Heine Westenfluss]] and [[Yzak Joule]].

Despite what the casual mecha anime [[otaku]] may think, the Gouf [i]"is not a [[Zaku]] boy, not a Zaku...".[/i] (ザクとは違うのだよ、ザクとは!)

title: chris_redfield
body:
[b]Chris Redfield[/b] is a Special Operations Agent (SOA) of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA), of which he is a founding member. Formerly, he served in the US Air Force; before moving on to law enforcement as a member of the RPD's Special Tactics And Rescue Service's (S.T.A.R.S.) Alpha Team. After S.T.A.R.S. were disbanded following the Raccoon City Incident, he and his partner, [[Jill Valentine]], became members of a Private Regional Biohazard Containment Unit (BCU), and took part in the fall of Umbrella in 2003. 

Chris is the older brother of [[Claire Redfield]] and one of few survivors of the mansion incident, during the Arklay Mountains outbreak in 1998. In addition to his qualification to pilot fixed-wing aircraft, Chris has been trained strictly in several fighting techniques like [[close-quarters combat]], is an expert in knife and firearm combat, and is also gifted with great accuracy.

Also notorious for punching a boulder in the climax of [[Resident Evil 5]].

h4.Appearance
Chris is a [[muscular male|muscular man]] with [[black hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. His appearance varies throughout the series.

* [[Resident Evil 1]]: Chris wears a [[police uniform]] with [[white shirt]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[fingerless gloves]], and black boots.
* [[Resident Evil 5]]: Chris has a [[green shirt]], [[gloves]], [[grey pants]] and a [[green footwear|green shoes]]. His appearance changes noticeably, looking much more muscular compared to Resident Evil 1 .
* [[Resident Evil 6]]: Chris wears a similar outfit to the ones he wore in Resident Evil 5, albeit he sports a [[grey pants]], [[green shirt]], [[bulletproof vest]] and [[gloves]].
* [[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]: In Resident Evil 7: biohazard, Chris design changed to a less muscular body and a [[brown hair]], he sports a [[black jacket]], [[gloves]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[black shoes]] and [[knee pads]]. 
* [[Resident Evil Village]]: Chris has a much more matured appearance in Resident Evil Village, he sports a [[black coat]] along with [[black shirt]], [[black pants]], [[gloves]] and black shoes.

h4. See also

* [[Chrisposting (meme)]]
other_names: クリス・レッドフィールド

title: matsuura_kanan
body:

body:
A dish consisting of [[spaghetti]], pasta sauce, and [[meatball|meatballs]] mixed together. Contrary to popular belief in cartoons and other media, Spaghetti and Meatballs is not a traditional Italian dish but a Italian-American dish as its creation was the result of early Italian immigrants combining two different dishes from Italy (Spaghetti with pasta sauce and small meatballs) and using ingredients available in their new home in the United States like extra beef which is plentiful in America.

title: chidejika
body:
Chidejika is a [[mascot]] created as a spokesperson for the [[Japan Commercial Broadcasters Association]] as a preparation for Japanese TV stations to switch to digital programming by July 24, 2011. Chidejika is an upright-walking deer wearing a yellow leotard.

The name actually means "terrestrial digitalization." The chi (地) means earth. Deji (デジ) is short for digital. Jika (ジカ) means deer. 

The mascot was created after the association dropped its original spokesperson, SMAP's Kusanagi Tsuyoshi, following his arrest for indecent exposure. Kusanagi was later reinstated, thus sharing the spokesperson position with Chidejika.

h4. See also

* [[Analoguma]]

title: armored_personnel_carrier
body:
A [[ground vehicle]] designed to transport [[soldier]]s and equipment into a combat zone.

APCs are fundamentally different from [[tank]]s. Generally speaking, APCs have lighter armor (still strong enough to resist bullets and shrapnel) compared to tanks. They have lighter armament because of their focused transport purpose and for the sake of mobility. Most commonly, APCs are armed with [[machine gun]]s or automatic [[grenade launcher]]s. It can either have wheels or [[caterpillar tracks]], while tanks are always tracked. Some can be amphibious.

Not only the [[military]], [[police]] tactical units also operate it. Sometimes APCs can be utilized as [[ambulance]], especially in battlefield (see post #1085064).

h4. List of APCs

* [[aavp-7a1|AAVP-7]]
* [[BTR-4 Bucephalus]]
* [[BTR-40]]
* [[BTR-60]]
* [[BTR-80]]
** [[BTR-90]] [tn]Larger version of the BTR-80 vehicle, fitted with a BMP-2 turret.[/tn]
* [[M113]]

* [[Stryker (afv)|]]

title: michael_knight
body:
[spoiler][quote][i]A man... who does not exist....[/i][/quote][/spoiler]

[b]Michael Knight[/b] is a the fictional protagonist character from the American adventure and [[science fiction]] TV series [[Knight Rider]] released in the 80s. 

Played by "David Hasselhoff":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hasselhoff , Michael is a high-tech modern crime fighter assisted by [[K.I.T.T]]., an advanced artificially intelligent, self-aware and nearly indestructible [[robot]] sports [[car]]. 

He is the primary field agent in the pilot program of his public justice organization, the Foundation for Law and Government (FLAG). 

Michael Knight is a special type of hero, a "modern [[knight]]" who avoids violence whenever possible and generally refrains from using melee weapons or firearms although he is actually a [[Vietnam War]] veteran proficient in [[martial arts]], [[close-quarters combat]] combat and the use of .38 [[revolver]]s and the [[MAC-10/11|MAC-10]] [[submachine gun]].

Michael [spoiler]was actually born Michael Arthur Long and was a LAPD detective working undercover, when he was shot in the face during a case and left for dead. Given a new face via facial reconstructive surgery by the FLAG organization, Long was resurrected as Michael Knight and deployed as their agent (as seen in the series pilot episodes).[/spoiler] 

h4. See also

* "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Knight_(Knight_Rider)_

title: kusanagi_motoko
body:
[b]Major Kusanagi Motoko[/b] is the main character of the [[Ghost In The Shell]] [[cyberpunk]] series.

Major Kusanagi is the serious and very competent squad leader of [[police|Public Security Section 9's counter-terrorist and anti-crime unit]].

The Major is a full body [[cyborg]] with short hair with long sidelocks. Her hair color changes from series to series; from blue in the original manga (and [i]Arise[/i]), black in the movies, to purple in [i]S.A.C.[/i] Her eye color also changes, being blue (movies), green or red depending on the show. She is often seen wearing a pink [[leotard]] with pink [[thighhighs]], black [[bodysuit|battle armor]], or a yellow [[police uniform|police officer's uniform]].

The Major is also an expert in systems hacking, infiltration, [[close-quarters combat]], [[martial arts]], and is extremely proficient with many types of ballistic weapons.

title: eve_online
body:
A science-fiction MMORPG developed by Icelandic company CCP Games. It is currently the only single-shard MMORPG in existence, meaning all players share a single world (called New Eden) of over 14,000 star systems, running on the gaming industry's most powerful server.

Players take control of a 'capsuleer', an augmented human (there are no alien species in the universe, with the possible exception of the reclusive Jove, who were originally humans as well, but have undergone extensive genetic modification, resulting in what is practically a new species) whose consciousness is transferred to a clone in the event of death, making the capsuleer immortal. Capsuleers travel in small capsules (hence the name) that protect them from various dangers in space, and which, in turn, are docked into larger ships, creating a conduit between the capsuleer brain and the ship systems in order to pilot the ship.

Expansions used to be issued twice a year, but towards the end of 2014, CCP Games switched to a release cycle of 4-6 weeks between expansions.

The game is (in)famous for its steep learning curve, stemming from the many opportunities and possibilities players are faced with, all of which are available from day one.

h4. External links
* "Website":http://www.eveonline.com

title: nakayama_racecourse
body:
Horse racecourse in Funabashi, Chiba. As one of the two JRA racecourses (the other beig [[tokyo racecourse|Tokyo]]) in the Tokyo area, it is home to a number of graded races, most notably the Satsuki Sho and Arima Kinen.

title: droopy_dog_(cartoon)
body:
This is a series of animated shorts from 1943 to 1958 featuring the titular [[Droopy]] character by cartoonist Tex Avery. The character would later appear in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows. On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between Tom and Jerry shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

title: droopy
body:
[[toon (style)|Cartoon]] character created by Tex Avery, an animator who worked for [[metro-goldwyn-mayer|MGM]], first appearing in 1943.

Droopy is an [[personification|anthropomorphic]] white [[basset hound]] with droopy jowls, [[half-closed eyes]], and [[floppy ears]]. He was the protagonist in his own set of [[Droopy Dog (cartoon)|]] shorts from 1943 to 1958 by cartoonist Tex Avery, and would later make appearances in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows.

On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between [[Tom and Jerry]] shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

h4. See also

title: foreign_disciples_(fate/grand_order)
body:
Major antagonists in the second arc of [[Fate/Grand Order]], seven servants summoned by the Alien God, [[U-Olga Marie]], to assist the [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]] in replacing greater human history with that of the Lostbelts. [spoiler]It turns out that unbeknownst to her, U-Olga Marie is also one of the disciples rather than the mastermind.[/spoiler] This tag applies if [b]at least 3[/b] are present in an image.

The disciples include:
* The God, [[U-Olga Marie]]. [spoiler]Manifested by mistake but repurposed to serve as the overseer for the other disciples. Initially believed to the Alien God itself.[/spoiler]
* The Priest, [[Rasputin (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Crypters.[/spoiler]
* The Malignant Incarnation, [[Ashiya Douman (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Lostbelt Kings and make sure none of the Lostbelts would overtake the [[Olympus (fate/grand order)|Greek Lostbelt]].[/spoiler]
* The Atlas Slayer, [spoiler][[Senji Muramasa (fate)|]]. Summoned to prevent [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]'s plot to destroy the Alien God.[/spoiler]
* The Detective, [spoiler][[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]]. Summoned to help Chaldea defeat [[Goetia (fate)|]] and the first 6 Lostbelts. Had his memories wiped and defected to Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Professor, [spoiler][[James Moriarty (Ruler) (fate)|]]. Summoned to kill the traitor [[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]] and then take control of Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Count, [spoiler][[Alessandro di Cagliostro (fate)|]]. Summoned to observe Chaldea.[/spoiler]
[[Koyanskaya (fate)|]] was initially believed by Novum Chaldea to be one of the disciples before being revealed to be an independent party working alongside them. For tagging purposes she may be included in the count.

h4. See Also
* [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]]

title: crypters_(fate/grand_order)
body:
Major antagonists in the second arc of [[Fate/Grand Order]], looking to supplant proper human history with their Lostbelts. Previously members of Chaldea's A-Team, who were killed during the inciting incident of the first arc and subsequently revived by the Alien God. This tag applies if [b]at least three[/b] are present in an image.

The seven Crypters are:
* [[Kadoc Zemlupus]], supervising the [[Anastasia (lostbelt) (fate/grand order)|Russian Lostbelt]] with his servant [[Anastasia (fate)|]]
* [[Ophelia Phamrsolone]], supervising the [[Gotterdammerung (fate/grand order)|Scandinavian Lostbelt]] with her servant [spoiler][[Surtr (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Akuta Hinako]], supervising the [[S I N (fate/grand order)|Chinese Lostbelt]] with her servant [spoiler][[Prince of Lan Ling (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Scandinavia Peperoncino]], supervising the [[Yugakshetra (fate/grand order)|Indian Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Ashwatthama (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Kirschtaria Wodime]], supervising the [[Atlantis (fate/grand order)|Greek Lostbelt]] with his servants [[Caenis (fate)|]], [spoiler][[Castor (fate)|]], and [[Pollux (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Beryl Gut]], supervising the [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|British Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Morgan le Fay (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Daybit Sem Void]], supervising the [[Nahui Mictlan (fate/grand order)|South American Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Tezcatlipoca (fate)|]][/spoiler]

h4. See Also
* [[Foreign Disciples (fate/grand order)|]]

body:

An excavated artillery [[mobile suit]] dating back to the Dark History, it has high firepower due to the backpack-mounted five-barrel gatling gun. Others armaments include a vulcan gun on the left side of its head and an arm-mounted shield with integrated beam saber emitter for close-quarters combat.

title: moana_(movie)
body:
Moana is a 2016 American animated musical fantasy adventure film produced by Walt Disney Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. The film was directed by John Musker and Ron Clements, co-directed by Chris Williams and Don Hall, and produced by Osnat Shurer, from a screenplay written by Jared Bush, and based on a story conceived by Clements, Musker, Williams, Hall, Pamela Ribon, and the writing team of Aaron Kandell and Jordan Kandell.
The film stars [[the rock (dwayne johnson)|Dwayne Johnson]] and Auliʻi Cravalho in her film debut as the voice of [[moana waialiki|the eponymous character]] and also features the voices of Rachel House, Temuera Morrison, Jemaine Clement, Nicole Scherzinger, and Alan Tudyk. It features original songs written by Lin-Manuel Miranda, Opetaia Foa'i, and Mark Mancina, and an original musical orchestral score also composed by Mancina. The film is set in ancient Polynesia and tells the story of Moana, the strong-willed daughter of a chief of a coastal village, who is chosen by the ocean itself to reunite a mystical relic with the goddess Te Fiti. When a blight strikes her island, Moana sets sail in search of Maui, a legendary demigod, in hopes of returning the relic to Te Fiti and saving her people. The screenplay takes inspiration from Polynesian myths.

title: zorro
body:
A fictional character created in 1919 by American pulp writer Johnston McCulley, appearing in works set in the Pueblo of Los Angeles in Alta California. He is typically portrayed as a dashing masked vigilante who defends the commoners and Indigenous peoples of California against corrupt, tyrannical officials and other villains. His signature all-black costume includes a [[black cape]], a hat known as a sombrero cordobés, and an [[eye mask]] covering the upper half of his face. 

Often considered the original American superhero, his antics would inspire both Superman and Batman.

title: moana_waialiki
body: Moana of Motunui is the title character of the 2016 Walt Disney Animation Studios film [[Moana (movie)|]]. Created by directors Ron Clements and John Musker, Moana is voiced by Hawaiian actress and singer Auliʻi Cravalho. As a toddler, she is voiced by Louise Bush. Moana returns in the sequel film Moana 2, which premiered in November of 2024, again voiced by Cravalho, as well as a live-action remake film, in 2026, in which she will be portrayed by Catherine Laga'aia.

title: maui_(moana)
body: Maui is a demigod of South Pacific legends. Despite his status, Maui finds himself torn between the worlds of humanity and deity, feeling "stuck in the middle". Nevertheless, he finds enjoyment in showcasing his godlike abilities to others.

title: kogal
body:
[b]Kogal[/b] (コギャル), a substyle of [[Gyaru]] (ギャル), is a [[fashion]] trend among young female Japanese high school students.

They follow the trends of gyaru fashion in their heavy makeup (especially around the eyes), sometimes [[tan]] skin, use of English-influenced slang (kogyarugo or コギャル語), coloured (and often bleached) hair, and trendy gyaru style fashion. Since they are school girls, they use their [[school uniform]] as their fashion statement, often wearing their uniform skirts very short and paired with [[loose socks]].

If there aren't any obvious signs of kogal (school uniform, [[loose socks]], [[scrunchie]], etc) then it's recommended to just tag the image with the more general [[gyaru]].

body: Black Adam, real name Teth-Adam , is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. He was created by Otto Binder and C. C. Beck, and first appeared in the debut issue of Fawcett Comics' The Marvel Family comic book in December 1945. Since DC Comics licensed and acquired Fawcett's characters in the 1970s, Black Adam has endured as one of the most popular archenemies of the superhero [[shazam|Captain Marvel / Shazam]] and the Marvel Family alongside Doctor Sivana and Mister Mind.

title: dayflower
body:
[b][i]Commelina[/i][/b], commonly called dayflower, is a genus of [[flower]]ing plants in the family [i]Commelinaceae[/i]. Commonly represented by [i]Commelina communis[/i] (Asiatic dayflower), native to East and Southeast Asia.

Commelinas are small flowers that are usually blue, but they also come in shades of white, yellow, purple, and pink. The flowers emerge from a boat-like sheath called a spathe that surrounds the flower stem.  Common species, such as the Asiatic dayflower, have a distinctive appearance: The flowers appear to have only two petals at the top, but there is actually a third, inconspicuous white petal at the bottom. They also have a distinctive pistil and stamens that curve upward.

h4. Examples
* !asset #24009824: Flower
* !asset #24010375: Flower and its spathe

title: tutankhamun_(fate)
body:
Archer-class Servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. One of the most famous Pharaohs of Ancient Egypt, Tutankhamun acceded to the throne at 9 years of age. During his reign he undid the shift of Ancient Egyptian religion caused by Akhenaten, who is believed to have been Tutankhamun's father. Tutankhamun's reign ended when died around age 18.

Tutankhamun was made famous in modern times by the discovery of his tomb in 1922. Compared to a lot of other pharaohs, Tutankhamun's tomb was largely undisturbed, and a lot of its contents, including treasures and his undisturbed mummy, were left intact. This discovery led to a renewed interest in Ancient Egypt by the public. The deaths of various individuals who were involved in the excavation of his tomb led to popular rumors regarding the "curse of the pharaoh".

title: tatara_kogasa
body:
The "Cheery Forgotten Umbrella". 

Stage 2 mid-boss and boss, as well as Extra Stage mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Undefined Fantastic Object]][/i], and Stage 3 mid-boss of [i][[Ten Desires]][/i]. A [i]karakasa[/i] youkai who frequently tries (in vain) to surprise humans. She carries her [[purple umbrella|purple]] [[karakasa obake]] with a [[tongue]] almost always sticking out, although there is some debate as to whether the girl or the umbrella (or both) is the real Kogasa. Fanworks often depict her under the mercy of [[Kochiya Sanae]] due to the latter's scathing words against her back in UFO.

Due to similarities in her style of dress to [[Kazami Yuuka]] (designated by [[ZUN (artist)|]] as "youkai moe"), along with her being perceived as a highly moe character in her own right, Kogasa is often referred to by fans as "the new youkai moe."

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24008618
* !asset #24008619

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]] and [[heterochromia]] with [[blue eyes|blue]] and [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[white shirt]] with [[juliet sleeves]], a [[blue vest]], a [[blue skirt]], and [[geta]]. In [[Wild and Horned Hermit]] she wears a [[frilled capelet|frilled]] [[blue capelet]] instead of her vest.

title: patterned_hair
body:
Hair with a pattern that would be impossible to replicate on real hair. Usually [[multicolored hair]].

Think of, for example, painting some stars on your hair. Whenever it moves, the star would break up into smaller hair strands.
As such, gradient hair and streaked hair can be replicated, but print hair cannot.

h4. See Also
* [[Unmoving pattern]]

title: wicker_man
body:
An ancient celtic druidic means of sacrifice, a large effigy in the shape of a man is built out of straw, where the condemned or simply slaves are put within and set ablaze.
The only known source of the wicker man's existence is from the writings of Gaius Julius Caesar and earlier writings by Posidonius the historian.

For the Noble Phantasm wielded by [[Cu Chulainn (Caster) (fate)|]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]], use [[Wicker Man (fate)]].

body:
A [[tennis]]-themed sports (and action) manga and anime series written and illustrated by [[Konomi Takeshi]]. It was serialized in [[Weekly Shounen Jump]] from 1999 to 2008. Localized as [b]The Prince of Tennis[/b] outside Japan.

The series is famous for an absurd amount of violence that is best compared to martial arts manga, with superhuman abilities, special moves, and life-threatening injuries. This unusual approach of sports manga is intentional on behalf of Konomi, who wanted it to be a departure from other popular sports manga and anime series at that time.

title: witness_holes
body:
"The term 'witness holes' generally refers to the small openings on the back or side-face of a handgun magazine allowing operators to visually confirm how many cartridges are loaded. Most modern semi-automatic handguns come standard with magazines featuring witness holes. It may also refer to the hole drilled in the top of a pistol barrel chamber so a user may visually confirm if there is a round chambered. This serves as a type of loaded-chamber indicator (LCI) but has no mechanical parts and does not allow for confirmation in low-light conditions when compared to a traditional LCI."

—SIG Sauer Glossary https://www.sigsauer.com/glossary/witness-holes/

title: meta_knight
body:
Meta Knight is a popular character in the [[Kirby_(series)|Kirby series]] and is the second of [[Kirby]]'s rivals, the first being [[King Dedede]]. He follows a code of honor, often providing Kirby with a sword to battle with (only breaking that code when he's not in control of himself, or when the situation is dire), and fights using a golden spiked sword called [[Galaxia (sword)|]]. Meta Knight is also shown to help Kirby sometimes.
 
In the [[kirby:_right_back_at_ya|anime]], he's definitely on Kirby's side, helping him fight against the evil Demon Beasts created by the Holy [[Nightmare (kirby)|]] Company that Dedede buys from them. He shows some relationships with one of Kirby's friends, [[Fumu (kirby)|]], seeing her as a rare source of intelligence. He's also a Star Warrior, having been one before Kirby and having been one of the few survivors of the war between the Galaxy Soldier Army and the Holy Nightmare Company. 

He is also playable in the [i][[Super Smash Bros.]][/i] games, starting with [i]Brawl[/i]. In [i]Brawl[/i] specifically, he is notorious for being a "god tier" character, which was addressed in the later [i]Smash[/i] games.

title: halberd
body:
A popular and versatile [[polearm]]. Its main distinguishing features are a head consisting of an [[axe]] blade, a [[spear]]head, and a hook or angled spike opposite the axe.

While the term halberd refers specifically to the medieval/renaissance European polearm, similar polearms such as the knightly poleaxe/pollaxe and Chinese [[qinglong ji]] also fall under this category.

Not to be confused with [[Meta Knight|Meta Knight's]] [[halberd_(airship)|signature battleship]].

h4. See also

title: light_fixture
body:
Also known as a Luminaire, a light Fixture is a device that holds a light source. 

While  usually permanent, they differ from light Fittings, as Fixtures aren't fused to the building they're on, and can usually be swapped out.

Light fixtures examples: Desk Lamps,  ceiling fans lights, LED exit signs, fluorescent light fixtures, ceiling Strip lights

title: yakumo_yukari
body:
The "Youkai of Boundaries". Phantasm Stage boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]] and later a recurring playable character.

A powerful youkai of at least 1200 years of age, reputedly older than [[Gensokyo]] itself. Nominally responsible for guarding the border between Gensokyo and the outside world, but is frequently sleeping or slacking around, leaving her work to her shikigami [[Yakumo Ran]] and Ran's own shikigami [[Chen]].

Yukari has the power to manipulate boundaries, as well as create [[gap (touhou)|]]s, leading to her nickname "Sukima". However, she frequently holds back her powers and most of the time she only goes as far as playfully dragging any unsuspecting human from the outside world into Gensoukyou.

in [[Silent Sinner in Blue]] she has two pet crows - [[Zenki (touhou)|]] and [[Goki (touhou)|]].

Besides her servants, she is friends with [[Ibuki Suika]], [[Saigyouji Yuyuko]] (whom she knew from as early as the latter's days as a human) and [[Hakurei Reimu]] (the other barrier guardian, whom she sometimes pesters). Also hinted to be [[Morichika Rinnosuke]]'s business partner and supplier of items from the outside world. Yukari has an as-yet undefined connection to [[Maribel Hearn]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #8183476: Usual Appearance #1
* !post #3666559: Usual Appearance #2
* !post #2978699: [[Antinomy of Common Flowers]]

h4. Related Pools

* Pool #1970: God Damn It, Yukari! - Yukari being a troll, usually with her [[gap (touhou)|]] powers.
* Pool #4099: Good Work, Yukari! - Yukari using her powers for good
* Pool #22787: Yukari the mom - Yukari acting motherly to Reimu or another character in her own way

h4. See also

title: let_me_solo_her
body:
Also known as [b]Klein Tsuboi[/b], a legendary [[Elden Ring]] [[tarnished (elden ring)|player]] with a summon sign outside [[malenia blade of miquella|Malenia]]'s boss fight.  Fights naked except for a [[pot on head|pot on their head]].  As his name suggests, is capable of soloing a co-op boosted Malenia without assistance from the summoner.

A screenshot of "this":[https://www.reddit.com/r/Eldenring/comments/u22zpa/heres_to_an_absolute_legend_let_me_solo_her/] particular Reddit post started the legend, and a screenshot of it shared outside of the website made it popular overrall.

On May 10th, 2022, Let Me Solo Her has soloed Malenia for the 1000th time.

With the release of [[Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree]], they changed their player name to Let Me Solo Them, facing the DLC's most challenging boss, [spoiler][[Promised Consort Radahn]][/spoiler].

h4. See also

Her outfit consists of a black [[crop top]] exposing her [[underboob]]s, [[pleated dress|pleated]] [[black dress]], [[black pantyhose]], [[black footwear|black]] [[thigh boots]], and a [[black hairband]]. Her [[rigging]] consists of two of her four planned 203 mm triple gun mounts on a dragon-like automaton. 

The fourth shipgirl introduced as part of the sixth wave of Priority Ships, [i]Hindenburg[/i] is basically an upscaled version of [[Roon (Azur Lane)|]], using the same 203 mm triple mounts, but her hull is based off the [i]Admiral Hipper[/i]-class to accommodate an extra fourth gun mount and four 533 mm quad [[torpedo tubes]]. Another note is that her size and displacement is similar to a battleship.

title: wrecking_crew
body:
A 1985 puzzle game released for the [[NES|Nintendo Entertainment System]] and the second [i]Wrecking Crew[/i] game. It's based on the arcade game of the similar name that released a year prior, [i]Vs. Wrecking Crew[/i], but focuses more on a single player puzzle game aspect than the competitive multiplayer of it's arcade counterpart. 

[[Mario]] & [[Luigi]] are demolition men who are tasked to destroy all the breakable walls in a given level to clear the stage (called "Phases"). They must find a way to accomplish this while navigating the roaming monsters hot on their tail, frequent fireballs spawning and a rival demolition man [[Foreman_spike|Spike]] trying to break the wall they're near to knock them down.

A stage based on this game was added to [i][[Super Smash Bros.]] for Wii U[/i].

title: daicon_iv
body:
An animated short produced by the [[Daicon]] Film group for the 22nd Annual Japan National SF Convention, [b]Daicon IV[/b], in 1983. 

The short they produced for this convention started with a recap of the original short [[Daicon III]] and continued the adventures of the protagonist, who now becomes the [[Daicon Bunny Girl]]. The quality of the animation in this short clip was much higher and impressive than that of the previous film.

The action was set to the song "Twilight" from the band [i]Electric Light Orchestra[/i]. The use of this song, however, was unlicensed, preventing the short from being officially released on DVD, making the limited laserdisc release of the Daicon shorts very rare and highly sought after.

This short firmly established Daicon Film as a talented new anime studio. The studio changed its name to [[Gainax]] two years later.

h4. Links

* "The opening for Daicon IV":[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-840keiiFDE]

* [[Daicon 33]]

body:

It was created by a studio formed in the early 1980s called [[Daicon]] Film. Daicon film would eventually become [[Gainax]] Studio a few years later.

While this animated short was ambitious, its animation was rough and low-quality.

title: poutine
body:
A dish of [[french fries]] and cheese curds topped with a brown [[gravy]].  It emerged in [[Quebec|Québec]], [[Canada]] in the 1950's, though it's exact origin remains unknown.  It since gained popularity in the rest of Canada becoming a national comfort food.

In the US a similar dish called Disco Fries exists, originating from the US state of New Jersey.  The primary difference between it and poutine is that it is made using shredded mozzarella cheese instead cheese curds.  The dish's exact origin date is unknown, but it was named in the 1970's after the late night customers coming in from disco clubs.

h4. External links

title: tuatara
body: Tuatara (Sphenodon punctatus) are reptiles endemic to New Zealand. Although resembling most [[lizard]]s, they are part of a distinct lineage, the order Rhynchocephalia. Their name derives from the Māori language, and means "peaks on the back". The single species of tuatara is the sole surviving member of its order, which originated in the Triassic period around 250 million years ago and which flourished during the Mesozoic era.

title: turtle
body:
[b]Turtles[/b] are reptiles famed for their slow pace, longevity and [[shell]]s. Most turtles are able to retract into their shells for protection.

Turtles are occasionally depicted as [[oversized animal|massive]] in size, sometimes [[island turtle|large enough]] to carry [[city|cities]], or even worlds.

title: pterosaur
body: Flying reptiles of the Mesozoic. Not a [[dinosaur]].

title: alligator
body: A very large reptile, a [[scales|scaly]] quadruped with a long [[crocodilian tail|tail]] and very powerful jaws. Often seen in the southeastern [[United states|United States]].

title: ano_hi_mita_hana_no_namae_wo_bokutachi_wa_mada_shiranai.
body:
あの日見た花の名前を僕達はまだ知らない。, lit. [i]"We still don't know the name of the flower we saw that day."[/i], abbreviated as [i]AnoHana[/i].

A Spring 2011 anime by [[A-1 Pictures]] and directed by Nagai Tatsuyuki, to be released in America as "Anohana: The Flower We Saw That Day".

Five years have passed since the Super Peace Busters, a group of six friends, dissolved following the tragic death of one of their own, [[Honma Meiko]]. Now [[hikikomori|a reclusive teen]], the group's de facto leader [[Yadomi Jinta]] gets a visit from Meiko's ghost, urging him to reassemble the gang to help her fulfill a wish so she may pass onto the afterlife. Slowly, they bring back the rest of the group: [[Anjou Naruko]], who remained in touch with Jinta as a classmate, [[Matsuyuki Atsumu]], a handsome top-scorer and his schoolmate [[Tsurumi Chiriko]], and [[Hisakawa Tetsudou]], a wanderer who takes part-time jobs to fund his travels.

h4. Characters

* [[Yadomi Jinta|Yadomi "Jintan" Jinta]]
* [[Honma Meiko|Honma "Menma" Meiko]]
* [[Anjou Naruko|Anjou "Anaru" Naruko]]
* [[Tsurumi Chiriko|Tsurumi "Tsuruko" Chiriko]]
* [[Matsuyuki Atsumu|Matsuyuki "Yukiatsu" Atsumu]]
* [[Hisakawa Tetsudou|Hisakawa "Poppo" Tetsudou]]

h4. External links

* "Official Site":http://www.anohana.jp/
* "[i]AnoHana[/i] on Wikipedia":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ano_Hi_Mita_Hana_no_Namae_o_Bokutachi_wa_Mada_Shiranai 
* "[i]AnoHana[/i] on pixpedia (Eng)":http://en.dic.pixiv.net/a/We+Still+Don%27t+Know+the+Name+of+the+Flower+We+Saw+That+Day

title: lacey_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Lacey[/b], known as [b]Taro[/b] (タロ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon sv|Pokémon Scarlet and Violet]][/i]'s [i]The Indigo Disk[/i] DLC.

Lacey is a member of Blueberry Academy's Elite Four and specializes in Fairy-type Pokémon.

Lacey is [[Clay (Pokemon)|]]'s daughter, as confirmed by [[Nemona (pokemon)|]] in their [[League Club Room]] interaction.

She has [[arched bangs]] and [[mismatched eyebrows]].

She is often depicted with [[x arms]], referencing some of her scenes in the game. Her catchphrase is "[[it's just not right!]]".

body:
[b]Sonia[/b] is a character introduced in [[pokemon swsh|Pokemon Sword and Shield]].

Sonia is a new professor researching the legends of Galar and has already published a book with her findings. She’s adventure buddies and childhood friends with [[Leon (pokemon)|]]. Her only known Pokemon is [[Yamper]].

She has [[green eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[orange hair|hair]] with [[heart hair ornament|hearts]] worn in a [[side ponytail|ponytail]]. title: piers_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Piers[/b], known as [b]Nezu[/b] (ネズ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon swsh|Pokémon Sword and Shield]][/i].

This Galar Gym Leader who loves Dark-type Pokémon is also a well-known singer and songwriter. Many of his fans were charmed by his melancholic vocal quality.

He has [[pale skin]], [[green eyes]] with [[grey eyeshadow]], and [[long hair|long]] [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[black hair|black]] and [[white hair]] with [[hair over one eye|bangs over one eye]]. He wears a [[shirt]] under a [[cropped jacket|cropped]] [[white jacket]], a [[belt]], [[mismatched gloves]], [[bike shorts]], and [[boots]].

title: nessa_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Nessa[/b], known as [b]Rurina[/b] (ルリナ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon swsh|Pokémon Sword and Shield]][/i].

This Gym Leader from Galar is also a popular model. She grew up playing with Water-type Pokémon thanks to her parents’ influence and is good friends with [[Sonia (pokemon)|]].

She has  [[dark-skinned female|dark skin]], [[aqua eyes|aqua]]/[[blue eyes]] with [[blue eyeshadow|eyeshadow]], and [[long hair|long]] [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[black hair|black]] and [[aqua hair]] with a [[single hair bun|bun]]. She wears [[hoop earrings|earrings]] and an [[earclip]], a [[necklace]], an [[armlet]], a [[belly chain]], [[bike shorts|spats]], a [[dynamax band|wristband]], [[single glove|a]] [[partially fingerless gloves|glove]], and [[white footwear|white]] [[sandals]].

title: gloria_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Gloria[/b], known as [b]Yuuri[/b] (ユウリ) in Japan, is the female player character in [i][[pokemon swsh|Pokémon Sword and Shield]][/i].

Gloria is full of courage and up for any challenge. She is slightly mischievous and enjoys playing outdoors, and she loves curry just as much as she does Pokémon battles [tn](official bio)[/tn]. 

She has [[brown eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[bob cut]] [[brown hair]]. She wears a [[green headwear|green]] [[tam o' shanter]], a [[pink dress|pink]] [[collared dress|dress]] under a [[grey cardigan|grey]] [[cable knit]] [[hooded cardigan]] both with [[buttons]], [[green socks|green]] [[plaid socks|plaid]] [[socks]], [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]], and a [[brown bag|brown]] [[backpack]] 

Her [[Pokemon Adventures]] counterpart is [b]Casey Shield[/b].

title: guzma_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Guzma[/b] is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

He is the strong leader of a group of toughs in Alola called Team Skull. The group's rowdy members obey him, and his kindness has earned their devoted respect [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Golisopod]].

He has [[grey eyes]], [[undercut]] [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[white hair|white]] and [[black hair]], and an [[arm tattoo]]. He wears [[yellow-framed eyewear|yellow-framed]] [[sunglasses]] on his [[eyewear on head|head]], a [[black jacket|black]] [[short sleeves|short sleeve]] [[hooded jacket]], a [[white shirt]], [[black pants]], and [[white footwear|white]] [[shoes]].

[b]Kahili[/b] is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

A genius pro [[golf|golfer]] with a stoic personality who competes all over the world, she is also a diligent member of the Elite Four who never neglects Pokémon battles.

She has [[grey eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[light blue hair]] with an [[ahoge]]. She wears a [[visor cap]], a [[shirt]], [[orange socks|orange]] [[kneehighs]], [[shoes]], and [[holding golf club|carries]] a [[golf club]].

title: nanu_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Nanu[/b], known as [b]Kuchinashi[/b] (クチナシ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

This Island Kahuna works as a police officer in the Alola region. He appears lazy, but he is truly skilled in Pokémon battles and also deeply compassionate.

He has [[red eyes]] and [[grey hair]]. He wears an [[open jacket|open]] [[short sleeves|short sleeve]] [[black jacket]], a [[red shirt]], a [[z-ring]], [[pants]], and [[flip-flops]].

title: olivia_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Olivia[/b], known as [b]Lychee[/b] (ライチ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

This Island Kahuna is trusted like a big sister by her island's residents, thanks to her compassion and strength in battle. The jewelry shop she runs also handles fossils. Her signature Pokemon is [[Lycanroc (midnight)|]].

She is [[dark-skinned female|dark skinned]], has [[black eyes]] with [[bright pupils]], [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] fashioned with [[swept bangs]], [[pink lips]], and [[aqua nails|aqua]] [[nail polish|fingernails]] and [[toenail polish|toenails]]. She wears [[earrings]], numerous [[bangle|bangles]], [[anklet|anklets]], [[thighlet|thighlets]] and [[neck ring|neck rings]], a [[bead necklace]], numerous [[diamond (shape)|diamond-shaped]] [[gem|gems]], a [[sleeveless]] [[pink shirt|pink]] [[crop top]] that reveals [[sideboob]], [[purple shorts|purple]] [[short shorts]], and [[pink footwear|pink]] [[high heels]].

title: sophocles_(pokemon)
body:
Sophocles is a character introduced in [[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]]. He is one of Alola's Trial Captains, specializing in the Electric type. In Sophocles' trial, the player battles a Totem [[Vikavolt]]. In [[pokemon usum|Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon]], they fight a Totem [[Togedemaru]] instead.

Sophocles inherited the position of captain from his cousin, [[Molayne (pokemon)|]], who he shares a close bond with. He is into mechanics, having invented various machines, and is the founder of the Festival Plaza. However, he is quite shy, and afraid of the dark. [spoiler]Sophocles is one of the trainers who can challenge the player for the title of Champion.[/spoiler]

In the [[pokemon (anime)|anime]], Sophocles is also one of [[ash ketchum|Ash]]'s classmates. He is a intelligent but shy boy who became fascinated with space at a young age.

Japanese name: [b]Maamane[/b]

title: kiawe_(pokemon)
body:
Kiawe is a character introduced in [[pokemon sm|Pokemon Sun and Moon]]. He is one of Alola's Trial Captains, specializing in the Fire type. In Kiawe's trial, the player battles a Totem [[Salazzle]]. His signature Pokémon is an [[Alolan Marowak]].

Kiawe is a young man who studies the traditional dances of the Alola region, and dreams of becoming a professional fire dancer. The player can meet and battle him in the Battle Tree.

In the [[pokemon (anime)|anime]], he is also one of [[ash ketchum|Ash]]'s classmates. He is a passionate, hot-blooded, and competitive Trainer and a doting big brother to his little sister, [[Mimo (pokemon)|]].

title: kukui_(pokemon)
body:
Prof. Kukui is a character in [[Pokemon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]], and Alola's resident Pokémon expert. He is a passionate man who specializes in Pokémon moves. He is married to [[Burnet (pokemon)|Prof. Burnet]].

He is also known as [b]The Masked Royal[/b] ([b]Royal Mask[/b] in the Japanese version), a famous masked wrestler and star of the Battle Royal Dome.

[spoiler]Kukui later creates Alola's own Pokémon League, and is the last challenge the protagonist overcomes before becoming the League's first champion.[/spoiler]

In the [[pokemon (anime)|anime]], Kukui is a teacher at the Pokémon School that Ash attended. He let him stay at his house.

body:

Mallow is a captain on Akala Island in Alola and works at a restaurant where she hones her skills as a chef. Her cooking is unique but popular among some [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Tsareena]]. 

She has [[dark-skinned female|dark skin]], [[green eyes]], and [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and in [[twintails]]. title: roxie_(pokemon)
body:

title: hogwarts_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] design from the [[Harry Potter (series)|]] series, worn by students at the Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

The uniform typically consists of a [[grey sweater]] or [[cardigan]] over a white [[dress shirt]] and black [[pants]] or a [[black skirt]]. A black [[hooded cloak]] goes over their clothes. Both the inner lining of the cloak and the [[necktie]] and various accessories will be in the student's house color.

Back in the late 19th century, when [[Hogwarts Legacy]] happens, the uniform had [[plaid pants]] for the boys and [[long skirt|long]] [[plaid skirt]]s for the girls.

h4. House colors
* [[Gryffindor]]: red and gold
* [[Ravenclaw]]: blue and grey
* [[Hufflepuff]]: yellow and black
* [[Slytherin]]: green and silver

h4.See also

* [[List of Uniforms]]

title: shinkansen
body:
The Shinkansen (Japanese: 新幹線, lit. 'new main line'), colloquially known in English as the bullet train, is a network of [[high-speed train|high-speed railway]] lines in Japan. It is operated by five [[Japan Railways]] Group companies. The popular English name [i]bullet train[/i] is a literal translation of the Japanese term [i]dangan ressha[/i] (弾丸列車), a nickname given to the project while it was initially discussed in the 1930s. The name stuck because of the original 0 Series Shinkansen's resemblance to a bullet and its high speed. (from Wikipedia)

!asset #23220925

title: ajinomoto
body:
Japanese multinational food and chemical corporation, most well-known internationally for its [[monosodium glutamate]] (MSG) product, from which the company derives its name, Aji-No-Moto (literally "essence of taste").  Alongside MSG and other condiments/seasonings, the company also produces processed foods such as instant noodles (ala [[instant ramen]] and pasta) and instant soups, frozen foods, coffees, cooking oils, TV dinners, sweeteners, amino acids and pharmaceuticals, among other things. In particular it is the world's largest producer of aspartame, with a 40% global market share.

They also produce [[Knorr (brand)|]]-branded products in Japan under license.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajinomoto

title: blaine_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Blaine[/b], known as [b]Katsura[/b] (カツラ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i].

This old man with a passion for trivia is known as the hotheaded quiz master. He's a Fire-type Gym Leader with a veteran Trainer's skill and a researcher's knowledge [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Arcanine]].

In his [[pokemon frlg|FRLG]] outfit, he is [[old man|old]], [[bald]], and has a [[white hair|white]] [[mustache]]. He wears [[round eyewear|round]] [[sunglasses]], a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[grey shirt|shirt]], an [[orange necktie|orange]] [[poke ball print|print]] necktie, a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[lab coat]], [[purple pants|pants]] with a [[belt buckle|buckled]] [[black belt|belt]], and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]].

title: giovanni_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Giovanni[/b], known as [b]Sakaki[/b] (サカキ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i], serving as the series' recurring and main antagonist.

This leader of the expansive Team Rainbow Rocket enterprise, which aims to use Pokémon to rule the world, believes Pokémon are no more than tools [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Rhyperior]].

He has [[black eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]]. He wears a [[grey shirt|grey]] [[turtleneck]] shirt under a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[v-neck]] [[black jacket]] which has the Team Rocket [[logo]] emblazoned on the front, [[black pants]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

body:
[b]Blue[/b], known as [b]Green[/b] (グリーン) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i].

This highly skilled, powerhouse Trainer prominent in Kanto is the grandson of the famous Professor Oak. [[Red (pokemon)|]] is both his lifelong rival and his best friend [tn](official bio)[/tn].

In his [[pokemon hgss|HGSS]] outfit, he has [[brown eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[spiked hair|spiky]] [[orange hair]]. title: lana_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Lana[/b], known as [b]Suiren[/b] (スイレン) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

Lana is an avid fisher and one of the captains of Akala Island. She loves her family and is constantly helping the family business or babysitting her twin sisters [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Araquanid]].

She has [[blue eyes]] with [[bright pupils|bright]] [[white pupils|pupils]] and [[no sclera]], [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]], and [[freckles]]. She wears a [[yellow hairband|hairband]], a [[one-piece swimsuit|swimsuit]] [[swimsuit under clothes|under]] a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[white shirt|shirt]] with a [[blue sailor collar|blue collar]], [[blue pants|blue]] [[wave print]] [[capri pants|pants]], and [[flip-flops]].

title: frankenstein's_monster
body:
A monster created by Dr. [[Victor Frankenstein]] by unspecified means.

Most modern depictions of Frankenstein's monster are based on the "1931 adaptation":https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0021884/, in which the monster was stitched together from parts of corpses and animated by electricity from a lightning storm. Monsters based on this film tend to have angular features, prominent [[stitches]], and [[bolt (hardware)|bolts]] drilled into the head or neck. Later depictions from the era of color film gave the monster [[grey_skin|grey]] or [[green skin]].

h4. See also

* [[Frankenstein]]

* [[monster]]
* [[undead]]
* [[Tag Group:Legendary Creatures]]

title: amelie_planchard
body:
Character from [[Strike Witches: Katayoku no Majo-tachi]]

A Sergeant from Gallia serving in the [[Isle of Wight Detachment Group]]. A very shy and crybaby girl, known for her crush on [[Perrine H. Clostermann]], and for being [[Wilma Bishop]]'s girltoy.

Her weapon is a Bren Light Machine gun Mk 1. Her familiar is a European rabbit, and she's based on Henri Planchard.

title: javanese_text
body:
Posts that contain text written in Javanese, either in Latin or its own Javanese script.

The Javanese language is an Austronesian language. It is spoken mostly on [[Java]], in [[Indonesia]].
Its closest relatives include [[sundanese_text|Sundanese]], [[madurese_text|Madurese]] and [[balinese_text|Balinese]] with [[malay_text|Malay]] and, therefore, [[indonesian_text|Indonesian]] being its distant relatives.

h4. See also

* [[Tag group:Text]]

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Javanese language":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javanese_language
* "Wikipedia: Javanese script":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javanese_script

title: tiny_green_mall_wizard
body:
[b]Tiny Green Mall Wizard[/b], also known as the Wizard Gnome, is a character created by TikToker "crawly_possessed" with which he dresses in a fake white beard, green robes and a white cone-shaped hat while crawling through stores in a mall. The TikToker previously went viral for the Crawling In Public trend in which he invited his followers to come crawl through a mall in Warsaw, Poland with him. The creator posted his first video as the Tiny Green Mall Wizard in late June 2024.

Since then Crawly has engaged in racism, hate speech, staged vandalism, real vandalism and overall aggressive behavior which coupled with his earlier harassment of mall workers earned him rightful bans on both TikTok and Kick. On November 29th 2024 he was apprehended by Polish Border Guard to begin a deportation procedure.

title: couple
body:
Two persons who are shown to be [b]mutually[/b] attracted to each other. That is to say, don't add this tag if one of the group is uncertain or shying away.

h4. Notes

* Do not add this tag based on canonicity. A picture with a canon couple who are not doing anything couple-like should not have this tag.
* Do not use this tag for all pictures with consensual sex/[[happy sex]]. There must be indication that the two involved are in love or have affection for one another.
* Both persons must be present in the picture. A hand or a penis is not a person.
* Please add [[hetero]], [[yaoi]], [[yuri]], [[other with female]], [[other with male]], [[other with other]], [[cuntboy]] or [[futanari]] to describe the type of couple.

title: goomboss
body:
Boss character introduced in [i][[Paper Mario 64]][/i], and later incorporated into [i][[Super Mario 64 DS]][/i] and [i][[Mario Kart DS]][/i]. 

Formerly known as the [b]Goomba King[/i], he is a large [[Goomba]] with a [[crown]], crazy [[ringed eyes]] and red-and-white [[striped pants]]. He has large, distinctive singular white [[facial hair]] on each side of his face.

title: madame_clairvoya
body:
A portrait ghost to be captured in [i][[Luigi's Mansion]][/i]. 

Known as the [b]Freaky-Fortune Teller[/b], she can tell the future by connecting with the spirit world and peering into her crystal ball. If [[Luigi]] brings her [[Mario]]'s lost items she will slowly uncover his whereabouts and the secrets of the mansion.

Her notable trademarks are having [[long_hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[blue skin]], and [[glowing_eyes|glowing]] [[yellow eyes]] that [[solid_eyes|lack pupils]]. She wears a [[red dress]], a [[gold necklace]] and big [[hoop_earrings|earrings]]. Both her head and her [[mouth_veil|mouth]] are covered in [[purple veil]]s.

She is the only Portrait Ghost who is not an enemy and volunteers to be captured, as she apparently prefers the "peace" of being in the painting.

title: kaenbyou_rin
body:
The "Traffic Accident of Hell". Stage 4 mid-boss, Stage 5 mid-boss and boss and Stage 6 mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Subterranean Animism]][/i]. Also known as "Orin" (お燐) to differentiate her from the earlier, concept-only character [[Satsuki Rin]].

A [i]kasha[/i] (monster [[cat girl|cat]]) responsible for transporting corpses on her [[wheelbarrow]] to the Hell of Blazing Fires to regulate its heat. Having learned of [[Reiuji Utsuho]]'s new power and her naive ambition to conquer the surface world, and fearing punishment from their master [[Komeiji Satori]], Rin sent evil spirits above the ground to warn any able fighter to face this threat. Apparent master of the so-called "[[zombie fairy (touhou)|Zombie Fairies]]". Occasionally depicted as a necrophiliac. She appears to have befriended [[Chen]] in [[Foul Detective Satori]], and passed her talent for finding and retrieving dead bodies to her.

h4. Appearance
* !post #6586882

She has both [[cat ears|cat]] [[extra ears|and]] [[pointy ears|human-ish ears]], [[red hair]] in [[twin braids]] tied with [[black bow|black]] [[hair bow]]s, [[blunt bangs|blunted bangs]], and [[two tails|two]] [[cat tail]]s. Her outfit is a [[green dress|green]] or [[black dress]] with either [[puffy short sleeves]] or [[juliet sleeves]] but almost [[frilled dress|always]] [[frilled sleeves|frilled]], a [[black ribbon|black]] [[leg ribbon]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]]. Often accompanied by her [[floating skull|floating]] and [[flaming skull]]s.

Her [[kaenbyou rin (cat)|cat form]] is as a [[black cat]] with [[two tails]], occasionally [[flame-tipped tail|flame-tipped]].
h4. See also

* "Nyan Clan of Gensokyo":/pools/17046

h4. External links

body:
[[Wario Land]] character and the main antagonist of [i][[Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3]][/i] and [i][[Wario Land II]][/i]. 

Leader of the Black Sugar Gang pirates. She steals treasure from all around the world and hordes her ill-begotten gains in Syrup Castle, located on Kitchen Island.

In her appearances in [i]Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3[/i] and [i]Wario Land II[/i], she's seen wearing a cyan one-piece outfit with yellow sashes throughout. In her reappearance in [i][[Wario Land: Shake It!]][/i], she's been given a purple top and bandana, black pants and a red skull belt with it.
